    "explanation": "Given sequence of chemical equation is<br><br><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1l8hra7fj/6f5799ff-33ff-4ec9-9169-c9625804a404/5e592af0-3d0b-11ed-9b24-3751e41e0789/file-1l8hra7fk.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1l8hra7fj/6f5799ff-33ff-4ec9-9169-c9625804a404/5e592af0-3d0b-11ed-9b24-3751e41e0789/file-1l8hra7fk.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"WB JEE 2018 Chemistry - Carbonyl Compounds Question 7 English Explanation 1\"><br>The structural formula of C<sub>8</sub>H<sub>6</sub>Cl<sub>2</sub>O(M) will be<br><br><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1l8hr8izt/27c0c8c0-8c38-42fa-b5a2-f556567587d0/2fa9b8a0-3d0b-11ed-9b24-3751e41e0789/file-1l8hr8izu.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1l8hr8izt/27c0c8c0-8c38-42fa-b5a2-f556567587d0/2fa9b8a0-3d0b-11ed-9b24-3751e41e0789/file-1l8hr8izu.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"WB JEE 2018 Chemistry - Carbonyl Compounds Question 7 English Explanation 2\"><br>The various step involves in the above road map can be explain as follows<br><br>Step - I : it involves the formation of an amide on reaction of ammonia and acetyl chloride so, M must be<br><br><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1l8hr8izt/27c0c8c0-8c38-42fa-b5a2-f556567587d0/2fa9b8a0-3d0b-11ed-9b24-3751e41e0789/file-1l8hr8izu.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1l8hr8izt/27c0c8c0-8c38-42fa-b5a2-f556567587d0/2fa9b8a0-3d0b-11ed-9b24-3751e41e0789/file-1l8hr8izu.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"WB JEE 2018 Chemistry - Carbonyl Compounds Question 7 English Explanation 3\"><br>Step = II : It involves the Hofmann-bromamide reaction.<br><br><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1l8hrc8b8/b667d1a3-14b7-4be2-9303-bc915ca4b2c1/96a58d40-3d0b-11ed-9b24-3751e41e0789/file-1l8hrc8b9.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1l8hrc8b8/b667d1a3-14b7-4be2-9303-bc915ca4b2c1/96a58d40-3d0b-11ed-9b24-3751e41e0789/file-1l8hrc8b9.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"WB JEE 2018 Chemistry - Carbonyl Compounds Question 7 English Explanation 4\"><br>In this reaction, migration of an alkyl or aryl group takes place from carbonyl carbon of the amide to the N-atom. So, C<sub>8</sub>H<sub>8</sub>ClNO must be an amide with structural formula.<br><br><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1l8hrdbnq/343357ef-845e-484d-9606-6fcf5643d2f3/b50a9e60-3d0b-11ed-9b24-3751e41e0789/file-1l8hrdbnr.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1l8hrdbnq/343357ef-845e-484d-9606-6fcf5643d2f3/b50a9e60-3d0b-11ed-9b24-3751e41e0789/file-1l8hrdbnr.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"WB JEE 2018 Chemistry - Carbonyl Compounds Question 7 English Explanation 5\">",
